# Flight Test Log

Record of all test flights for the RC Ornithopter project.

---

## Test Phase 1 — Manual RC Only (Basic Controller)

**Controller:** `flight_controller_basic.ino`  
**PID:** Disabled  

| Test # | Date | Duration | Throttle % | Outcome | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1.1 | — | ~5s | 60% | Partial flight | Sustained lift achieved, very difficult to control pitch |
| 1.2 | — | ~8s | 65% | Crash | Pitch instability, no stabilization |
| 1.3 | — | ~12s | 62% | Partial | Manual correction possible but demanding |

**Findings:**
- Sustained flight is possible with manual control.
- Without pitch stabilization, the ornithopter requires constant pilot input to stay level.
- Gearbox shoulder joint identified as primary failure point.

---

## Test Phase 2 — PD Controller (Pitch Only)

**Controller:** `flight_controller_pid.ino` with `Ki = 0`  
**Gains:** `Kp = 1.0, Ki = 0, Kd = 0.4`

| Test # | Date | Duration | Throttle % | Outcome | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 2.1 | — | ~15s | 65% | Improved | Pitch noticeably more stable |
| 2.2 | — | ~20s | 68% | Good | 9 wing beats captured in level flight |
| 2.3 | — | ~30s | 70% | Successful | ~30 yards of steady flight, shut down manually |

**Findings:**
- PD controller (without integral) successfully stabilises pitch.
- Throttle limited to ~70% due to ESC 30A rating.
- At maximum throttle, wing spars develop resonance mode — avoid.
- Flapping vibration on MPU6050 manageable with foam mounting.

